# Framework Flow

```mermaid
graph TD
    Test -->|uses| Fixture
    Fixture -->|initializes| PageObjects
    PageObjects -->|use| Helpers
    Test -->|generates data via| Factory
    Test -->|integrates with| Mailinator
```
---
# Framework Design

## Page Object Model (POM)
Each page encapsulates:
- Locators
- Actions
- Assertions

Example:
```js
await homepage.goToProfile();
await profilePage.verifyProfileLoaded();
```

# Fixture
The fixture provides reusable setup and pre-configured test state.

Example:
```js
test('...', async ({ homepage }) => {
```

The homepage fixture:
- Navigates to the app
- Returns a ready-to-use Page Object

# Factory
The factory generates dynamic and unique test users.

Example:
```js
{
  newUsername: "edu123456",
  newEmail: "edu123456@mailinator.com",
  newPassword: "Password123!"
}
```
# Authentication Strategy
The auth files store session states to use in various projects to reuse

Example:
```js
await context.storageState({
  path: 'auth/existing-user.json',
});
```

This approach enables:
- Faster test execution
- Reuse of authenticated sessions across tests
- Customized user states for specific tests. For example, new vs. existing users, or users with different roles.


# Email Verification (Mailinator Integration)

 Example:
 ```js
await mailinator.openInboxByUsername(user.newUsername);
await mailinator.openActivationEmail(user.newEmail);
const activationPage = await mailinator.clickActivationLink();
```

This process handles:
- Inbox scoping
- Email selection
- Iframe interaction
- New tab navigation

---

# End-to-End User Flow

# Registration 
- Open login page
- Navigate to registration
- Submit new user details
- Open Mailinator inbox
- Activate account via email
- Set password (new tab)
- Verify first login
- Save credentials for reuse

# Profile Management
- Navigate to Profile of a stored user session
- Update profile details
- Change username (with revert)
- Change password (with revert)
- Validate UI elements (groups & qualifications)
- Error handling for nonvisible elements and unsuccessful updates

# Negative Tests
- Invalid username
- Invalid password

Example:
```js
await login.verifyInvalidLoginError();
```

---

# Test Structure:
Arrange в†’ Act в†’ Assert

# Reusability
- Page methods are reused across tests
- Login sessions are reused before each test begins
- Dynamic data generation

# Stability
- Explicit waits using expect()
- Handling optional UI (toasts, modals)
- Cleanup actions (closing tabs, reverting data)


# Highlights
- Real-world workflow automation
- Multi-system integration (App + Email)
- Clean, maintainable architecture
- Advanced Playwright usage (fixtures, storageState, multi-tab)


# Why This Framework?
This framework is designed to:
- Reduce test flakiness through controlled state management
- Enable parallel execution safely
- Support non-technical QA onboarding through clear structure
- Validate real user workflows, not just isolated UI components
- Account for unique quirks that can exist in applications